    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1975-04-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1975-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="41"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d41">
                <head>41. Memorandum From A. <persName corresp="#p_CAD1" type="from">Denis
                        Clift</persName> of the National Security Council Staff to Secretary of
                    State <persName corresp="#p_KHA1" type="to">Kissinger</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d41fn1">Source: Ford Library, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (<gloss target="#t_H1"
                            >H</gloss>–Files), Box <gloss target="#t_H1">H</gloss>–33, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> 215. Secret. Sent for action.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1975-04-03">April 3, 1975</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>US-Greek Base Negotiations</item>
                </list>
                <p>We are now approaching the second round of US-Greek base talks, scheduled to
                    begin in Athens on April 7.</p>
                <p>State, without White House clearance, has sent the message at Tab A<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d41fn2">Attached but not printed.</note> to Embassy Athens,
                    providing guidance for the talks.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> 215, U.S. Security Policy Toward
                        Greece,<note n="3" xml:id="d41fn3">
                        <ref target="#d33">Document 33</ref>.</note> was issued to ensure that
                    preparations for the talks would go forward in the <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> system, this bearing in mind such contentious interagency
                    issues as homeporting [<hi rend="italic">1 line not declassified</hi>].</p>
                <p>The <gloss target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> response<note n="4" xml:id="d41fn4">See
                            <ref target="#d40">Document 40</ref>.</note> worked a very useful effect
                    in that it brought <gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss> around and led to
                    interagency agreement [<hi rend="italic">2½ lines not declassified</hi>].</p>
                <p>The <gloss target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> response also reached the conclusion
                    that, despite the internal U.S. Navy decision to give up homeporting as soon as
                    possible, this “concession” to the Greeks should be in return for meaningful
                    Greek concessions. This quid pro quo approach has been weakened in the
                    instructions at Tab A; Navy clearly plans to give up homeporting in this round,
                    concessions or not.</p>
                <pb facs="0172" n="146" xml:id="pg_146"/>
                <p>The approach the U.S. Government is taking in these talks—[<hi rend="italic">less
                        than 1 line not declassified</hi>] to U.S.-Greek and Greek-<gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> linkages, to homeporting—involves interagency
                    policy issues that should be confirmed in a decision memorandum. I recommend
                    that action be taken on Log #1737, March 21, 1975, which forwarded the <gloss
                        target="#t_NSSM1">NSSM</gloss> 215 response together with a proposed <gloss
                        target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss>.<note n="5" xml:id="d41fn5">
                        <ref target="#d39">Document 39</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Recommendation</hi>
                </p>
                <p>That action be taken on the <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> forwarded with
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Log #1737.<note n="6" xml:id="d41fn6"
                        >The <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> was issued on April 8; see <ref
                            target="#d43">Document 43</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
